Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.43,0:01:09.76,Default,,0000,0000,0008,,{\fn华文楷体\fs20\1c&HE0E0E0&\blur3}宇宙:太空灾难{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.62,0:00:04.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}创世之初 冥冥之中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In the beginning, there was darkness...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.12,0:00:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}随着轰的一声{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and then, bang...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.25,0:00:09.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}诞生了无限膨胀的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}giving birth to an endless expanding existence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.46,0:00:11.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}时间 空间和物质{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}of time, space, and matter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.88,0:00:14.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}现在 所见超乎我们的想象{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Now, see further than we've ever imagined...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.38,0:00:16.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}超越了我们生存的限制{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}beyond the limits of our existence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.30,0:00:19.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这个空间我们称之为"宇宙"{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in a place we call "The Universe."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.10,0:00:25.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在太空里 威胁可以来自四面八方:{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In space, threats can come from any direction:{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.15,0:00:28.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}来自深太空的陨石{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}meteors from deep space...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.23,0:00:32.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}来自太阳的无形但致命的辐射爆{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}invisible but deadly bursts of radiation from the Sun...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.69,0:00:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其它星球上的山崩地裂{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}otherworldly landslides from above and Marsquakes from below.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.83,0:00:41.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}外太空是你作为人类最不想去的地方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Outer space is the last place you want to be as a human being.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.62,0:00:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}轨道上什么样的子弹比地球上更加致命?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}What makes fire more deadly in orbit than on Earth?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.21,0:00:47.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}人类暴露在...{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}What happens to someone...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:51.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}极端恶劣的外太空里有什么后果?{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}exposed to the harsh extremes of outer space?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.34,0:00:55.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}唾液 血液 会从液态变为气态{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The saliva, the blood, goes from a liquid state...to a gaseous state.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.43,0:01:00.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}系上安全带 准备应对《太空灾难》{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Buckle up and prepare for "Space Disasters."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.12,0:01:25.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}2030年{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The year is 2030.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.71,0:01:27.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}一群宇航员{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A crew of astronauts...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.33,0:01:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}按下了太空电梯的上行按钮{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}simply hits the "up" button in a space elevator.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.88,0:01:33.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}电梯将带他们登上飞船{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The elevator will bring them to their spacecraft...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.88,0:01:35.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}飞船已经在轨道上等候着他们{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which will meet them in orbit.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.38,0:01:38.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}他们庆幸自己{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}They're grateful they don't have to risk...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.13,0:01:40.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}不必冒火箭升空爆炸的危险{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the controlled explosion of a rocket launch.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.72,0:01:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我们现在已经能创造出碳纳米管纤维{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}We can now create carbon nanotube fibers...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.35,0:01:48.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其强度超过了钢铁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that are stronger than steel.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.23,0:01:51.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}信不信由你 它们的强度足以{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And believe it or not, they are strong enough...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.36,0:01:55.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}让太空电梯漂浮在太空中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}to keep a space elevator afloat in space...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.28,0:01:58.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这样你就能够一路攀升上天{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}so that you can literally climb your way into the heavens.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.99,0:02:05.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}6万英里缆绳固定住空间站{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The 60,000-mile cable is attached to the docking station...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.75,0:02:07.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它的运转速度与地球同步{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that revolves at the same rate as the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.67,0:02:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}类似于地球同步卫星{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Just like a geosynchronous satellite...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.00,0:02:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它停留在地面固定一点的上方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it stays over a fixed spot on the ground.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.34,0:02:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太空电梯是所有宇航员梦寐以求的{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}A space elevator would be any astronaut's dream.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.39,0:02:23.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}然而太空电梯之梦{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But the space elevator dream...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.35,0:02:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}同样也会变成一场噩梦{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}can also turn into a nightmare.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.73,0:02:31.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太空电梯必须固定在地球上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The space elevator has to be anchored to the Earth.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.94,0:02:35.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}但是如果遇上风暴会有什么后果{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}But what happens if we have storms...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.07,0:02:39.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}突然之间 锚具开始扯断{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and, all of a sudden, the moorings begin to snap?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.99,0:02:45.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}由于缆绳仍然固定在太空中{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}With the cable still attached up in space...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.70,0:02:47.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}它就会开始疯狂摆动{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}it will start swinging wildly...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.95,0:02:51.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}任意击打着数百英里外的物体{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}striking objects hundreds of miles away in any direction.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.88,0:02:56.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}也有可能 某些导航计算机{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It's also possible that some type of guidance computer...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.80,0:03:01.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}或推进器产生的问题会敲打偏离航向的太空平台{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}or thruster problem could knock the platform in space off-course...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.30,0:03:02.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在顶部扯断缆绳{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}snapping the cable at the top.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.01,0:03:09.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果此时正好有船员沿着缆绳上下{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}lf it happened while a crew was going up or down the cable...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.52,0:03:15.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那么他们就必定会遭遇生命中最后一次搭乘{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}they would be in for the last ride of their lives.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.15,0:03:21.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}6万英里缆绳 砸向地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}And the 60,000 miles of cable, hurtling toward Earth...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.49,0:03:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其长度足以缠绕地球{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}is long enough to wrap itself around the planet...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.16,0:03:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}几乎是赤道的3倍 造成大面积的破坏{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}almost three times at the equator, creating havoc over a wide area.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.96,0:03:35.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这不仅会对人类造成灾祸{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}It would be not only disastrous and dangerous...for the people involved...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.96,0:03:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而且 那样的东西所带来的动能{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}the kinetic energy of something like that...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.50,0:03:42.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}会鞭击大气层 给航行带来威胁{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}whipping through the atmosphere, would be a menace to navigation...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.68,0:03:47.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所以它会对于其中所有的人类系统{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}so it's going to have an inherent danger in it...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.10,0:03:48.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}带来潜在的危险{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that any human system has.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.18,0:03:53.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}这只是未来太空探险家所面对的N多{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}This is just one of many potential disasters...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.98,0:03:56.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}潜在灾难之一{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}facing future space explorers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.24,0:04:10.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}定居在太空中也会涉及巨大的危险{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Living in space will also involve grave dangers.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.96,0:04:14.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}月球或火星上的移民{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Colonies on the Moon or Mars...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.08,0:04:16.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}所面临的威胁来自四面八方{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}will be faced with threats from all directions...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.46,0:04:20.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}尤其是头顶上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}especially above...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.97,0:04:26.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}突然爆发的辐射高峰会致人于死地{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}where sudden spikes of radiation can turn deadly.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.56,0:04:34.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}如果我们漫步在月球表面{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}If we were walking around on the surface of the Moon...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.40,0:04:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}我想说我们的头号烦恼就是太阳耀斑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}I would say our number one concern should be solar flare.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.57,0:04:43.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}太阳爆发{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Sun erupts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.19,0:04:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}耀斑射出的质子会让宇航员送命{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The protons coming from that flare could kill an astronaut.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.99,0:04:51.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}最近20年里有过几次耀斑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There have been several flares over the last couple decades...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.04,0:04:54.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}其中 假如我们有宇航员呆在月球上{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}which, if we had had astronauts on the Moon...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.50,0:04:57.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}穿着宇航服四处活动 就会将他们置于死地{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}just walking around in a spacesuit, would have been lethal for them.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.09,0:05:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}在地球上 我们躲过了多数辐射{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}On Earth, we're protected from most radiation.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.88,0:05:10.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}地球的大气层和磁场 就像是保护盾{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Earth's atmosphere and magnetic field are like a protective fence...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.47,0:05:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}只让少量的粒子通过{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}letting only a fraction of particles through.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.48,0:05:16.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}而在月球或火星上 你就直接处在了一线{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}On the Moon and Mars, you are directly in the firing line.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.65,0:05:23.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}月球没有大气层或磁场{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Moon has no atmosphere or magnetic field.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.82,0:05:25.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}火星只有很少的大气{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}Mars has very little atmosphere...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.70,0:05:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}以及很弱的局部磁场{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}and only weak, localized magnetic fields.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.83,0:05:34.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}航天局认为太阳耀斑的威胁非同小可{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}NASA takes the solar flare threat seriously...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.79,0:05:38.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}因为它差一点害死阿波罗宇航员{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}because it has already come close to killing Apollo astronauts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.84,0:05:43.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}阿波罗登月宇航员相当幸运{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}The Apollo lunar landing crews were quite fortunate.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.67,0:05:48.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}1972年8月 有一次严重的太阳耀斑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}In 1972, in August, there was a major solar flare.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.09,0:05:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}他们称之为大太阳风暴的耀斑{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}There was what they call the Great Solar Storm...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.47,0:05:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}恰好就发生在了{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}that happened to just take place...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.01,0:05:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur3}那年4月的阿波罗16号任务与{\r}\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&\blur3}in between the Apollo 16 mission in April...{\r}
